The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                Rabin Panja, 32, who runs a tutorial agency, was arrested after he produced eight fake notes of Rs 500 denomination at a bank in Paikpara on Sunday. Police said Panja had turned up at the bank to deposit Rs 40,000. He claimed he was unaware how the fake currency got into the bundle of notes. Bank officials handed him over to Chitpur police station. This is the first time a person with no apparent criminal past has been arrested on the charge of possessing fake notes, said an officer.    A man died and a woman was injured in separate mishaps in the city on Monday. The man, in his 40s, died after falling off a speeding minibus on Old Court House Street, in front of Great Eastern Hotel, and hitting a pedestrian barricade. Police said he was hanging from the footboard of the overcrowded bus. Witnesses took him to Calcutta Medical College and Hospital where he was declared dead on arrival.   n the other mishap, a Matador knocked down 65-year-old Saraswati Kouri around 10am on Beleghata Main Road near Sarkar Bazar. Kouri was taken to NRS hospital with a leg injury. She was released after treatment. Both vehicles were seized.    A youth snatched a womans gold chain on a bus on route 44 on Monday. Police said Ruma Biswas, 30, was heading for College Street from Baguiati. While the bus was approaching Lake Town, a youth snatched the chain and jumped off the bus.    Passenger trains will not ply on the Kharagpur-Rourkela and the Kharagpur-Adra sections of South-Eastern Railway from 10pm to 5am till August 6 because of security reasons. The Howrah-Adra Chakradharpur Passenger, the Howrah-Adra-Bokaro Passenger and the Kharagpur-Tatanagar Passenger will remain cancelled till August 6.    The foundation stone for the Trinity Research Institute of Plastic Surgery, Burns and Trauma was laid in Convent Lane, Entally, on Monday. The 200-bed unit will have facilities for cosmetic and reconstructive surgery and other facilities.    Eleven supporters of the Burrabazar District Chhatra Parishad were arrested on Monday afternoon when they tried to demonstrate in front of Writers Buildings to protest the hike in power tariff.    Varun Bharthuar joined the South Eastern Railway as additional general manager on Monday. He was the additional general manager of East Central Railway.    A domestic help and her aide were arrested on Monday for stealing an ashtadhatu idol and a pair of earrings from the employers house in Panchanantala Lane under Gariahat police station the day before. The stolen booty was recovered.    Usuf Ali Mollah and Kutubuddin Mollah were arrested after residents of Salt Lakes ward 9 spotted them cutting trees on Monday night.            
